# Bell alert

This scenario creates one quiet tmux session and one session with a bell alert,
then launches `sesh`. The markdown transcript remains textual, and the linked
SVG snapshots cover row styling.

    :bins jj cat

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', and 'cat' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t set-option -g visual-bell both (success)
    :t set-window-option -g monitor-bell on (success)
    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :t new-session -d -s alert "printf '\\a'; cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s quiet "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 80 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0

The alert row should carry green pip styling in the linked SVG snapshot.

    :settle (settled)
    :k alert
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: alert
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close
▌⬤ alert                                                                       ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

![light](bell-alert.md.snap.1.light.svg)
![dark](bell-alert.md.snap.1.dark.svg)

The quiet row is not alerted and should not carry the green pip styling.

    :k C-u quiet
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: quiet
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close
▌⬤ quiet                                                                       ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

![light](bell-alert.md.snap.2.light.svg)
![dark](bell-alert.md.snap.2.dark.svg)

